 Subcategory: PR.AC-3: Remote access is managed
 Requirement: PR.AC-3.1 The organisation's wireless access points shall be secured.
 Guidance: Consider the following when wireless networking is used:
 â€¢ Changetheadministrative password upon installation of a wireless access points.
 â€¢ Set thewireless access point so that it does not broadcast its Service Set Identifier
 (SSID).
 â€¢ Setyour router to use at least WiFi Protected Access (WPA-2 or WPA-3 where
 possible), with the Advanced Encryption Standard (AES) for encryption.
 â€¢ Ensurethat wireless internet access to customers is separated from your business
 network.
 â€¢ Connecting to unknown or unsecured / guest wireless access points, should be avoided,
 and if unavoidable done through an encrypted virtual private network (VPN) capability.
 â€¢ Manageall endpoint devices (fixed and mobile) according to the organization's security
 policies.
