Function: PROTECT (PR)
 Category: Identity Management, Authentication and Access Control (PR.AC): Access to
 physical and logical assets and associated facilities is limited to authorized users, processes,
 and devices, and is managed consistent with the assessed risk of unauthorized access to
 authorized activities and transactions.
 Key Measure: Key Measure
 Subcategory: PR.AC-4: Access permissions and authorizations are managed, incorporating the
 principles of least privilege and separation of duties
 Requirement: PR.AC-4.1: Access permissions for users to the organizationâ€™s systems shall
 be defined and managed.
Guidance: The following should be considered:
 â€¢ Drawupandreview regularly access lists per system (files, servers, software,
 databases, etc.), possibly through analysis of the Active Directory in Windows-based systems,
 with the objective of determining who needs what kind of access (privileged or not), to what, to
 perform their duties in the organization.
 â€¢ Setupaseparate account for each user (including any contractors needing access) and
 require that strong, unique passwords be used for each account.
 â€¢ Ensurethat all employees use computer accounts without administrative privileges to
 perform typical work functions. This includes separation of personal and admin accounts.
 â€¢ Forguest accounts, consider using the minimal privileges (e.g. internet access only) as
 required for your business needs.
 â€¢ Permission management should be documented in a procedure and updated when
 appropriate.
 â€¢ Use'Single Sign On' (SSO) when appropriate.
