Function: PROTECT (PR)
 Category: Identity Management, Authentication and Access Control (PR.AC): Access to
 physical and logical assets and associated facilities is limited to authorized users, processes,
 and devices, and is managed consistent with the assessed risk of unauthorized access to
 authorized activities and transactions.
 Key Measure: Key Measure
 Requirement: PR.AC-4.3: Employee access to data and information shall be limited to the
 systems and specific information they need to do their jobs (the principle of Least Privilege).
 Guidance: The principle of Least Privilege should be understood as the principle that a security
 architecture should be designed so that each employee is granted the minimum system
 resources and authorizations that the employee needs to perform its function. Consider to:
 â€¢ Notallow any employee to have access to all the businessâ€™s information.
 â€¢ Limit the number of Internet accesses and interconnections with partner networks to the
 strict necessary to be able to centralize and homogenize the monitoring of exchanges more
 easily.
 â€¢ Ensurethat when an employee leaves the business, all access to the businessâ€™s
 information or systems is blocked instantly.
