Function: PROTECT (PR)
 Category: Identity Management, Authentication and Access Control (PR.AC): Access to
 physical and logical assets and associated facilities is limited to authorized users, processes,
 and devices, and is managed consistent with the assessed risk of unauthorized access to
 authorized activities and transactions.
 Key Measure: Key Measure
 Requirement: PR.AC-5.2: Where appropriate, network integrity of the organization's critical
 systems shall be protected by incorporating network segmentation and segregation.
Guidance: â€¢
 Consider creating different security zones in the network (e.g. Basic
 network segmentation through VLANâ€™s or other network access control mechanisms) and
 control/monitor the traffic between these zones.
 â€¢ Whenthenetwork is "flat", the compromise of a vital network component can lead to the
 compromise of the entire network.
