Function: IDENTIFY (ID)
 Category: Asset Management (ID.AM): The data, personnel, devices,
 systems, and facilities that enable the organization to achieve
 business purposes are identified and managed consistent with their
 relative importance to organizational objectives and the
 organization’s risk strategy.
Requirement: ID.AM-2.2: The inventory of software platforms and
 applications associated with information and information processing
 shall reflect changes in the organization’s context and include all
 information necessary for effective accountability.
 Guidance: The inventory of software platforms and applications should
 include the title, publisher, initial install/use date, and business
 purpose for each entry; where appropriate, include the Uniform
 Resource Locator (URL), app store(s), version(s), deployment
 mechanism, and decommission date.
