Function: IDENTIFY (ID)
 Category: Asset Management (ID.AM): The data, personnel, devices,
 systems, and facilities that enable the organization to achieve
 business purposes are identified and managed consistent with their
relative importance to organizational objectives and the
 organization’s risk strategy.
 Subcategory: ID.AM-3: Organizational communication and data flows are
 mapped
 Requirement: BASIC_ID.AM-3.1: Information that the organization stores
 and uses shall be identified.
 Guidance: • Start by listing all the types of information your
 business stores or uses. Define “information type” in any useful way
 that makes sense to your business. You may want to have your employees
 make a list of all the information they use in their regular
 activities. List everything you can think of, but you do not need to
 be too specific. For example, you may keep customer names and email
 addresses, receipts for raw material, your banking information, or
 other proprietary information.
 • Consider mapping this information with the associated assets
 identified in the inventories of physical devices, systems, software
 platforms and applications used within the organization (see ID.AM-1 &
 ID.AM-2).
 Documentation Score: 1
