Function: DETECT (DE)
 Category: Detection Processes (DE.DP): Detection processes and
 procedures are maintained and tested to ensure awareness of anomalous
 events.
 Subcategory: DE.DP-4: Event detection information is communicated
 Requirement: DE.DP-4.1: The organization shall communicate event
 detection information to predefined parties.
 Guidance: Event detection information includes for example, alerts on
 atypical account usage, unauthorized remote access, wireless
 connectivity, mobile device connection, altered configuration
 settings, contrasting system component inventory, use of maintenance
 tools and nonlocal maintenance, physical access, temperature and
 humidity, equipment delivery and removal, communications at the
 information system boundaries, use of mobile code, use of Voice over
 Internet Protocol (VoIP), and malware disclosure.
