Function: PROTECT (PR)
 Category: Data Security (PR.DS): Information and records (data) are
 managed consistent with the organization’s risk strategy to protect
 the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of information.
 Subcategory: PR.DS-7: The development and testing environment(s) are
 separate from the production environment
 Requirement: PR.DS-7.1: The development and test environment(s) shall
 be isolated from the production environment.
 Guidance: • Any change one wants to make to the ICT/OT environment
 should first be tested in an environment that is different and
 separate from the production environment (operational environment)
 before that change is effectively implemented . That way, the effect
 of those changes can be analysed and adjustments can be made without
 disrupting operational activities.
 • Consider adding and testing cybersecurity features as early as
 during development (secure development lifecycle principles).
 Documentation Score: 1
