Function: RECOVER (RC)
 Category: Communications (RC.CO): Restoration activities are
 coordinated with internal and external parties (e.g. coordinating
 centers, Internet Service Providers, owners of attacking systems,
 victims, other CSIRTs, and vendors).
Subcategory: RC.CO-2: Reputation is repaired after an incident
 Requirement: RC.CO-2.1: The organization shall implement a crisis
 response strategy to protect the organization from the negative
 consequences of a crisis and help restore its reputation.
 Guidance: Crisis response strategies include, for example, actions to
 shape attributions of the crisis, change perceptions of the
 organization in crisis, and reduce the negative effect generated by
 the crisis.
