Key Measures (KM)
 Access and Identity Controls
 · PR.AC-1.1 —Identities and credentials for authorized devices and users shall be
 managed.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-3.2 —Theorganization’s networks when accessed remotely shall be secured,
 including through multi-factor authentication (MFA).
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-4.1 —Access permissions for users to the organization’s systems shall be
 defined and managed.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-4.2 —Itshall be identified who should have access to the organization’s
 business-critical information and technology and the means to get access.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-4.3 —Employee access to data and information shall be limited to the systems
 and specific information they need to do their jobs (principle of Least Privilege).
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-4.4 —Nobodyshall have administrator privileges for daily tasks.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-5.1 —Firewalls shall be installed and activated on all the organization’s
 networks.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-5.2 —Whereappropriate, network integrity of the organization’s critical systems
 shall be protected by incorporating network segmentation and segregation.
