Governance, Processes, and Supply Chain Controls
 · ID.AM-6.1 —Information security and cybersecurity roles, responsibilities, and
 authorities within the organization shall be documented, reviewed, authorized, and
 updated in alignment with organizational internal roles and external partners.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-3.3 —Usagerestrictions, connection requirements, implementation guidance,
 and authorizations for remote access to the organization’s critical systems shall be
 identified, documented, and implemented.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-5.3 —Whereappropriate, network integrity of the organization’s critical systems
 shall be protected by:
 (a) Identifying, documenting, and controlling connections between system components.
 (b) Limiting external connections to the organization’s critical systems.
 Target Maturity Score: 3.00
 KMMaturity Score: 1.00
 Documentation Maturity Score: 1.00
 Implementation Maturity Score: 1.00
 · PR.AC-5.4 —Theorganization shall monitor and control connections and
 communications at the external boundary and at key internal boundaries within the
 organization’s critical systems by implementing boundary protection devices where
 appropriate.
