# NIS2 × CyFun Comprehensive Cross-Mapping (Belgium)
 This AI-ready knowledge base links the CyFun Framework SSOT controls to the
 Self-Assessment maturity criteria,
 the Evidence Register (Bewijzenregister), and NIS 2 / NIST contextual
 guidance.
 Structure per control: What (SSOT) → How well (Self-Assessment) → Proof
 (Bewijzenregister) → Context (NIS2/NIST).
 🧠 How the “Comprehensive Cross-Mapping” File Fits In
 1️⃣ It does not replace your other files
 The file does not overwrite or discard the original sources.
 Instead, it acts as a centralized knowledge spine — a semantic bridge
 between all your source documents:--------------------------------------------
| |Source File | |Role | |Relationship to the Cross-Mapping File |--------------------------------------------
| |CyFun Framework SSOT (Sheet1) | |Defines what the controls are (functions,
 categories, measures, guidelines) | |The cross-mapping references and
 integrates this content verbatim. |--------------------------------------------
| |CyFun Self-Assessment Tool V2025-08-04 | |Defines how maturity is measured
 (documentation + implementation) | |The cross-mapping extracts and links the
 corresponding scoring lines per control. |--------------------------------------------
| |Bewijzenregister [SSOT] | |Defines what evidence proves compliance | |The
 cross-mapping maps each control to its related proof requirements. |--------------------------------------------
| |BE-NIS2-RA-v20240108-healthcare | |Adds sector-specific Belgian NIS 2
 context | |The cross-mapping imports context and interpretation where
 relevant. |--------------------------------------------
| |NIST Categories– SSOT SUPPORT | |Connects CyFun → NIST → NIS 2 | |The
 cross-mapping creates the interoperability layer, aligning IDs to NIST CSF
 categories. |--------------------------------------------
| |CyFun mapping Public_v20240108 | |Provides naming and taxonomy consistency
 | |The cross-mapping normalizes control names and IDs using it. |
 2️⃣ Think of it as the “Knowledge Index”
 It’s like the table of contents and integrated reference for your entire
 framework.
 It doesn’t replace the originals — it points back to them in a harmonized,
 AI-readable way.
 When your AI bot needs to answer something like:
 “What documentation do we need to prove compliance with NIS 2 Article 21 for
 asset management?”
 It will:
 1. Use the Cross-Mapping file to find the correct control ID (ID.AM-1, ID.AM
5, etc.).
 2. See both the Self-Assessment and Evidence Register data linked to it.
 3. Pull supporting context from BE-NIS2-RA or NIST Categories based on that
 ID.
 4. Optionally, open the original files for detailed or updated references.
 3️⃣ The right workflow for your AI knowledge base--------------------------------------------
| |Layer | |Purpose | |Data Source |--------------------------------------------
| |Base knowledge (reference layer) | |Raw regulatory, framework, and
 evidence data | |All original files |--------------------------------------------
| |Cross-Mapping (semantic layer) | |Unifies and contextualizes data for
 reasoning | |NIS2_CyFun_Comprehensive_CrossMapping.txt |
--------------------------------------------
| |AI bot (reasoning layer) | |Understands user intent, retrieves relevant
 control segments, and builds answers | |Uses the Cross-Mapping as its primary
 lookup index, and the originals for deep retrieval |
 4️⃣ Why keep all the files
 * The cross-mapping is optimized for understanding and reasoning, not for
 archival fidelity or future updates.
 * If CCB releases a new version (e.g., CyFun Framework v2026), you can update
 individual source files and regenerate the cross-mapping automatically.
 * This keeps your system future-proof, modular, and easy to maintain.
 ✅ Summary
 * 🔗 The Cross-Mapping file is your central AI-readable map connecting all
 frameworks.
 * 📚 The original files remain the authoritative data sources for updates,
 evidence templates, or sector-specific details.
 * 🧩 The AI bot uses both: the Cross-Mapping for reasoning and sources for
 depth.
 ### Control ID: DE.AE-1
 FUNCTION: Detect
 CATEGORY: Anomalies and Events
 CONTROL & GUIDELINES (from SSOT):
 FUNCTIONS: Detect
 CATEGORY NAME CYFUN: Anomalies and Events
 SUBCAT ID CYFUN: DE.AE-1
 Maatregel: DE.AE-1.1
 SUB-SUBCATEGORIE: De organisatie moet ervoor zorgen dat een baseline van
 netwerkoperaties en verwachte gegevensstromen voor haar kritieke systemen
 wordt vastgesteld, gedocumenteerd en
 bijgehouden om gebeurtenissen te volgen.
 RICHTLIJNEN: • Overweeg lokale logging op al uw systemen en netwerkapparaten
 in te schakelen en deze gedurende een bepaalde periode te bewaren,
 bijvoorbeeld tot 6 maanden.
 • Zorg ervoor dat uw logs voldoende informatie bevatten (bron, datum,
 gebruiker, tijdstempel, enz.) en dat u voldoende opslagruimte hebt voor het
 genereren ervan.
 • Overweeg uw logs te centraliseren.
 • Overweeg de inzet van een Security Information and Event Management tool
 (SIEM) die de correlatie en analyse van uw gegevens vergemakkelijkt.
 SELF-ASSESSMENT MATURITY (from CyFun Self-Assessment Tool):
 DE.AE-1.3 — The organization shall ensure that a baseline of network
 operations and expected data flows for its critical systems is developed,
 documented, and maintained to track events.
 EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS (from Bewijzenregister):
 Sub-category: DE.AE-1
 Sub-sub-category: DE.AE-1.1
 NIS 2 / NIST CONTEXTUAL NOTES:
 CyFun Framework [SSOT CORE]: DE.AE-1.1 , DE.AE-2.1 , DE.AE-2.2 , DE.AE-3.1 ,
 DE.AE-3.2 , DE.AE-3.3 , DE.AE-4.1 , DE.AE-5.1 , DE.AE-5.2--
